# Git LFS — the replay regression reference bag (docset 05-logging-replay, M8 / T8.7, SWM-79).
#
# The checked-in reference MCAP the replay test (tests/replay/test_replay_regression.py) plays is a
# binary artifact tracked via Git LFS (design OQ-4) so the repo stays light and the bag's history is
# pointer-only. CI must check out with `lfs: true` (the replay-regression workflow does) — a bag
# whose LFS pointer fails to resolve makes the replay test fail loudly, not skip (design §4.4.5).
#
# Scope is intentionally narrow: only the reference bag under tests/replay/reference/, NOT every
# .mcap (operator bags under ~/patrol_bags are never committed). The `**` matches the bag's nested
# `patrol_reference/<bag>_0.mcap` layout (rosbag2 writes the .mcap inside a bag directory).
tests/replay/reference/**/*.mcap filter=lfs diff=lfs merge=lfs -text
